esenting Coinbase compliance with the New York Department of Financial Services in respect to Coinbase's BitLicense and Money Transmitter Licenses Act as a Compliance regulatory product liaison, working cross-functionally across Coinbase, particularly with product and legal teams Overseeing the development and execution of the global Compliance Testing & Monitoring (\"CMT) program and methodology Serve as an advisor to the organization, educating the business and helping them design and/or remediate controls in response to regulatory exam or CMT program findings?? Collaborate with internal and external audit assurance providers to maintain open lines of communication on assurance initiatives at Coinbase Oversee the continued development, and maintenance of the GRC Issues Use Case ensuring functional line of sight into issues remediation status Core compliance activities including policy review, where required Present CMT findings to senior compliance leadership and global and local entity Boards as required. P repare relevant board materials for quarterly parent company board meetings. Cross functional collaboration with the other Compliance and Legal roles on emerging regulations. What we look for in you (ie. job requirements): Strong communication skills and presence: ability to interface with regulators and product teams Work in a cross functional and matrixed environment Understanding of the Institutional space, both traditional finance and crypto market Nice to haves: Thorough understanding of block chain technology and crypto Knowledge of BitLicense and NY DFS Trust Company License requirements Experience either working inside a financial regulatory agency or managing regulatory compliance programs and examinations for a regulated financial institution Management experience in a matrixed environment and technology/fintech organization Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our j